## Project Context


### Architecture

- Blade pattern: each capability is a self-contained module with base.py (Protocol + ABC), models.py (Pydantic), factory.py (wiring), and one or more implementation files. All blades are optional extras in pyproject.toml.
  _`blades`, `patterns`_
- Exception hierarchy: all exceptions inherit from JackknifeError. Blade-specific: LLMError, StorageError, MemoryError, DataConnectorError, MCPError, AgentError, ScaffoldError. Always raise the most specific subclass.
  _`exceptions`, `patterns`_
- Task graph orchestration: NetworkX DiGraph where edges Aâ†’B mean 'B depends on A'. ready_tasks() returns PENDING tasks with all deps COMPLETED. Orchestrator runs up to max_parallel tasks concurrently with asyncio.gather().
  _`agents`, `orchestration`_
- Config via pydantic-settings. Each blade has its own *Settings class. Top-level Settings composes all blades. get_settings() is @lru_cache â€” call get_settings.cache_clear() in tests. All path fields must be absolute.
  _`config`, `settings`_
- Memory write queue: MemoryWriteQueue serializes concurrent writes to ChromaDB via asyncio.Queue. Multiple agents can enqueue concurrently; writes processed one at a time. Required because ChromaDB is not thread-safe.
  _`memory`, `concurrency`_
- LiteLLM is the only LLM provider implementation. Model string selects provider: gpt-4o-miniâ†’OpenAI, claude-3-5-sonnet-latestâ†’Anthropic, gemini/gemini-2.0-flashâ†’Google, ollama/llama3.2â†’Ollama. API keys via env vars.
  _`llm`, `providers`_
- All async I/O: sync third-party SDKs (ChromaDB, boto3, GCS, Azure, pandas, neo4j) are wrapped with asyncio.get_running_loop().run_in_executor(None, partial(fn, *args)). Native async SDKs (motor, redis.asyncio, SQLAlchemy asyncio, neo4j AsyncDriver) used directly.
  _`async`, `patterns`_

### Convention

- Commit message format (commitizen enforced): feat:, fix:, docs:, refactor:, test:, chore:, ci:. Never commit to main directly. Always branch â†’ commit â†’ PR.
  _`git`, `workflow`_
- CI/CD: ruff (lint+format), mypy strict, pytest with 80% coverage required. Pre-commit runs all three locally. GitHub Actions (test.yml) runs on every push/PR. publish.yml uses PyPI Trusted Publishing (OIDC) on version tags.
  _`ci-cd`, `quality-gates`_
- Use Poetry for all dependency management. Never use pip or python3 directly. Always: poetry run <cmd>.
  _`tooling`, `setup`_
